      "The moratorium would temporarily ban the construction, expansion, permitting, and site plan approval for data centers exceeding five megawatts of projected electrical load. That threshold covers the kind of large-scale AI and cloud-computing facilities that have drawn billions in investment to neighboring cities like Clinton, Ridgeland, and Madison County.",
