      "Smart Start Wellness Bash kicks off today in south Jackson: The Magnolia Medical Foundation is hosting the Smart Start Wellness Bash today from 9 a.m. to 3 p.m. at 3311 Terry Road, offering free health screenings, back-to-school bookbags and supplies, teacher resources, school uniforms, fresh produce, and games. The event is one of several community back-to-school efforts ahead of JPS’s July 29 start date. The district’s annual Beautification Day is set for July 17, and a ribbon-cutting for the newly renovated Brinkley Middle School (formerly Powell Middle School) is scheduled for July 27. The National Weather Service forecasts a high near 95 today with a heat index up to 105, so organizers advised attendees to bring water and plan for the heat.",
