      "The meetings come two weeks after the council's June 22 public hearing on data center zoning, where more than 20 people spoke and only one speaker voiced support for data centers, according to the Clarion Ledger. The Jackson Fire Department limited capacity to about 65 people in the council chambers that night, turning away roughly two dozen residents who stood in the hallway and listened through the building's speaker system.",
