      "Since then, the debate has accelerated. A company called Saxum Investment Group is seeking to rezone roughly 190 acres near Forest Avenue and Interstate 220 to I-1 light industrial, making the site data center-ready. The proposal later expanded to 230 acres, according to testimony at the June 22 hearing. The Planning Board postponed Saxum's rezoning request in May and again in June, with Zoning Administrator Ester Ainsworth saying it would not be fair to vote without new regulations in place.",
